1
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:33,200
Then let me do it.

2
00:02:33,280 --> 00:02:34,800
I'll steal the teddy bear.

3
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:37,560
PREVIOUS EPISODE

4
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:41,280
I don't want you putting yourself
at risk like that.

5
00:02:41,880 --> 00:02:45,120
I can't stand seeing my father
being humiliated like this either, Uncle.

6
00:02:45,720 --> 00:02:48,920
If we're doing this,
the first thing she has to do

7
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:53,440
is apply for the singing competition
at Darathong Music.

8
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,800
Alright, Village Head,
since we're old friends,

9
00:02:57,880 --> 00:03:01,720
- Yes
- Maria doesn't need to go audition

10
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:04,000
or do a voice test in the other room.

11
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:07,920
<i>Why did you come and fool me</i>
<i>Leaving me confused?</i>

12
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,720
Teacher,

13
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:12,000
isn't that Maria's voice?

14
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,920
I can't believe
that the kind-hearted Kamnan Pong

15
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,880
knows people who deal drugs.

16
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,160
I don't want to jump
to conclusions just yet.

17
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,440
These things, you have
to watch unfold over time.

18
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:40,640
Hello, everyone!
Today is Kamnan Pong's birthday.

19
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:43,360
Feel free to pick up your donations here.

20
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,760
Free stuff!

21
00:03:47,520 --> 00:03:48,920
What's available here?

22
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:51,760
FREE FOOD AND DRINKS
FOR PEOPLE OF KHOK TA YU

23
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:56,840
Why aren't you in line?

24
00:04:01,560 --> 00:04:02,400
Oh no!

25
00:04:04,240 --> 00:04:05,640
Who's trying to kill me?

26
00:04:06,360 --> 00:04:07,800
Is it you?!

27
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:12,560
You too, huh? You!

28
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:29,560
Thanks, you two. What are your names?

29
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:32,200
- I'm Chaiya.
- I'm Manat, Sergeant Yot's nephew.

30
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,080
- Sergeant Yot's nephew?
- Yes.

31
00:04:36,160 --> 00:04:38,000
So, are you two police officers?

32
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:44,760
No, we're YouTubers from Bangkok.

33
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:46,480
Actually, we're between jobs right now.

34
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:47,920
We came here to travel

35
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,000
and maybe make some content

36
00:04:50,080 --> 00:04:51,880
that could be useful for society.

37
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:53,880
YouTube? Good.

38
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,800
If there's anything you need, let me know.
I'm happy to help.

39
00:04:57,880 --> 00:05:00,360
- Don't hesitate.
- Thank you.

40
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:04,640
Hey, stop!

41
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,880
This is the police.

42
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:10,880
I need to search you.
Turn off the engine now! Get off the bike.

43
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:12,640
Quick!

44
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:16,280
- Come here.
- What's going on, Sergeant?

45
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,200
We got a report

46
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,640
that you guys are in possession of drugs.

47
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,320
- What are you talking about?
- I'm just telling you the truth.

48
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,880
Now, let me search you. Slowly.

49
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:28,920
This way.

50
00:05:39,400 --> 00:05:40,520
Think you're tough, huh?

51
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:43,720
Boss, there's trouble.

52
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:47,280
Hey, Chaiya!

53
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,400
CHECKPOINT

54
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:57,160
If you hurt my uncle, you'll regret it!

55
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,960
Uncle, are you okay?

56
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:28,000
I'm fine. Follow them!

57
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,160
Quick! Go, now!

58
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:03,440
You hurt my man, you're dead!

59
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,680
Take this!

60
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,200
Well? Come on.

61
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:08,640
Let's go.

62
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:16,280
Thanks a lot, Chaiya. Manat.

63
00:08:16,360 --> 00:08:19,240
I'll see you at home. Come here.

64
00:08:28,600 --> 00:08:31,080
<i>From now on</i>

65
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,320
<i>I'll stop being obsessed with you</i>

66
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:36,760
DARATHONG MUSIC

67
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:38,440
Maria!

68
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:40,120
I'm nervous!

69
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,799
This is my daughter, Boss.

70
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,919
She's got potential.

71
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:47,040
She has the right look too.
Here's what we'll do.

72
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:50,640
I'll put Maria's name
through to the final stage.

73
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:52,560
She'll skip the preliminaries.

74
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:53,720
Wow!

75
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:56,560
- Thank you, Boss.
- We're friends.

76
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:03,400
Hey, are you here
for the singing competition?

77
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,720
Yeah, I'm about to leave.

78
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:07,480
Oh my gosh, Poona.

79
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,960
Did your uncle
let you enter the competition?

80
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,720
Yes, he gave me permission.

81
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:16,760
Did you know, Poona,

82
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:19,480
that Miss Maria sang for the boss,

83
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,720
just for him, privately?

84
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:26,560
Yeah, someone of Miss Maria's level,
when applying for the competition,

85
00:09:26,640 --> 00:09:29,800
needs a special audience, you know.

86
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,320
Bet you're shocked!

87
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,240
I hope you make it through the rounds.

88
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:38,080
- Nice words!
- Correct.

89
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,600
I'm already in.

90
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:43,680
The boss has me set to win first place.

91
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,680
- She'll win!
- She'll get the prize.

92
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,840
Just wait until the real competition,

93
00:09:54,920 --> 00:09:56,440
I'll beat you for sure.

94
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,560
- You're so good!
- Really good!

95
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:03,160
Has the label already rigged the results?
I thought it was about talent.

96
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:06,560
Guess no talent means
you just play the connections game.

97
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:11,440
Watch your mouth! This is Darathong Music.

98
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,360
- A major label.
- Right.

99
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,480
Not your petty little band!

100
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:17,880
- You can't talk like that here.
- Exactly.

101
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:20,120
- I'm just saying what I heard.
- Alright, enough.

102
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,800
Let's not waste time arguing.

103
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:27,040
We'll settle this on stage.

104
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,440
See you, Maria.

105
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,720
Yeah, you'll definitely see me.

106
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:50,960
Wait, I thought Wilai
was supposed to meet us here.

107
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,480
Why hasn't she shown up yet?

108
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,520
I'll go buy coffee in the meantime.

109
00:10:57,600 --> 00:11:01,200
- Okay. I'll call her myself.
- Alright.

110
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,920
I'll have an iced coffee, please.

111
00:11:21,520 --> 00:11:23,720
Here you go. Thank you.

112
00:11:28,440 --> 00:11:30,880
- So good!
- I'll find something to eat--

113
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,480
Oh no.

114
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:39,440
- I'm so sorry!
- What's this? My shirt!

115
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,720
- You!
- You!

116
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,440
Hang on! Let's go to the police station.

117
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:50,000
Huh? Just spilled coffee
and you're taking me to the cops?

118
00:11:51,200 --> 00:11:54,480
Don't pretend you don't know.
You know exactly what you did.

119
00:11:54,560 --> 00:11:56,240
You ran away from me that night.

120
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:58,840
What are you talking about?

121
00:11:59,440 --> 00:12:01,640
- Let go of me!
- No, come with me!

122
00:12:01,720 --> 00:12:03,560
Hey, let go!

123
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:06,040
Take it! Throw it away!
I can't even drink it now.

124
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,320
Don't run away! Let me catch you first!

125
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:10,560
Geez!

126
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:17,960
Oops!

127
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:22,600
AGRICULTURAL PRODUCT PROCESSING FACTORY

128
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,760
What should I do? He's coming!

129
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:32,640
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

130
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:39,040
Where is she?

131
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:59,160
Hey! What are you doing in here?

132
00:12:59,240 --> 00:13:01,120
I'm looking for someone.

133
00:13:01,200 --> 00:13:02,280
Come to steal something?

134
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,040
What's wrong with you?

135
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,880
Hey!

136
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:13,880
Ugh.

137
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,280
Hey, stop!

138
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,520
Hey!

139
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:43,560
PROCESSED AGRICULTURAL PRODUCTS

140
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,120
Phew.

141
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,960
Hey.

142
00:13:56,560 --> 00:13:57,760
Hey, stop!

143
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:01,760
Hey!

144
00:14:15,960 --> 00:14:18,880
You didn't call me for all the fun, huh?

145
00:14:28,640 --> 00:14:32,280
Stop! Stop right now!
What's going on here?

146
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:37,040
This guy broke into the factory.
He's here to steal something!

147
00:14:37,120 --> 00:14:40,280
You're mistaken. I'm not here to steal,
just looking for someone.

148
00:14:40,360 --> 00:14:41,560
Looking for who?

149
00:14:42,400 --> 00:14:43,480
Is this the one?

150
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,640
Yeah, that's her.

151
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,120
Let go of me!
I haven't done anything wrong!

152
00:14:51,560 --> 00:14:54,040
Hey, what's the deal
with you and these guys?

153
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:55,760
It's this guy.

154
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:57,520
He's a pervert, harassing women.

155
00:14:58,120 --> 00:15:00,760
He grabbed my hand out of nowhere,
so I ran away.

156
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:03,240
Well then, I'll take them to the station.

157
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:07,520
Stop! This is my nephew! My nephew!

158
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,600
Hey, Sergeant.

159
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,000
Do you know these two guys?

160
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:13,640
Yeah, they're my nephews.

161
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:16,040
Don't arrest them.
It's just a misunderstanding.

162
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,440
But during the Agriculture Fair,

163
00:15:19,280 --> 00:15:21,880
they were chasing me.
It was the same just now.

164
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:25,200
How is this a misunderstanding, Sergeant?

165
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:31,920
Well, I thought you and your friend…

166
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,800
Her name's Maria.

167
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:39,040
Yeah, I thought you and Maria

168
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:41,160
planted the bombs at the Agriculture Fair.

169
00:15:42,040 --> 00:15:45,360
I'm just trying to be a good citizen
and turn you in.

170
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:46,400
Yeah, that's right.

171
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:51,840
Hey, Maria was caught
in the explosion too.

172
00:15:51,920 --> 00:15:54,320
Sornrak Darathong
had to step in and help her.

173
00:15:54,400 --> 00:15:56,320
How could she be involved
in planting bombs?

174
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:57,600
You're way off on this.

175
00:15:57,680 --> 00:16:01,920
Exactly, and I was caught
in the explosion that night too.

176
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,960
If I were involved with the bombers,

177
00:16:04,040 --> 00:16:07,040
I must be pretty stupid
to run right into the same explosion.

178
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:15,760
Alright, I get it now. I'm sorry.

179
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:20,080
I'm sorry too.

180
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:24,400
Now that we've apologized,
let's leave it at that.

181
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,400
No more trouble, alright?

182
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,040
Okay.

183
00:16:32,920 --> 00:16:35,040
Thanks so much for clearing things up.

184
00:16:36,360 --> 00:16:37,360
As for you,

185
00:16:38,280 --> 00:16:39,920
next time,

186
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:42,240
don't come anywhere near me.

187
00:16:54,160 --> 00:16:55,040
Poona, over here!

188
00:17:04,480 --> 00:17:06,880
- Hello, Aunt Wilai.
- Hello.

189
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:10,760
Sorry, I had a little issue
with an idiot earlier.

190
00:17:10,839 --> 00:17:12,560
But it's all cleared up now.

191
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:16,160
So, you signed up to sing, right?

192
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:17,119
Yes.

193
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:20,599
They had me sing live
in front of the judges.

194
00:17:20,680 --> 00:17:24,599
But they'll post the shortlist
on their website.

195
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:28,960
- Alright.
- Wilai, look over there.

196
00:17:29,560 --> 00:17:30,760
See that?

197
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,640
What's going on, Sergeant?

198
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:39,480
These two young guys here
caused some trouble,

199
00:17:40,120 --> 00:17:41,840
so I had to give them a little talk.

200
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:49,400
Hello, Kamnan Pong. Do you remember me?

201
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:52,440
- I remember you.
- This is my nephew, Kamnan.

202
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:55,800
- Which one is your nephew?
- That's me.

203
00:17:56,440 --> 00:17:57,960
I'm Sergeant Yot's nephew.

204
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:00,880
I've been free lately,
so I thought I'd come visit him.

205
00:18:02,120 --> 00:18:05,840
We're both unemployed right now.
If there's any work at this factory,

206
00:18:05,920 --> 00:18:06,960
we're happy to take it.

207
00:18:08,240 --> 00:18:09,360
Sorry.

208
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:13,560
This factory is part
of the community product group

209
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:17,800
that I built to help people in the village
earn a living.

210
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:22,400
Only people from this village
are allowed to work here.

211
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:25,360
I see. No problem.

212
00:18:25,440 --> 00:18:27,840
Ever since the incident 20 years ago,

213
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:30,360
Kamnan Pong hasn't been as cheerful
as he used to be.

214
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:33,200
He stopped managing
the music label he used to run

215
00:18:33,280 --> 00:18:35,720
and let Singha take over.

216
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,720
He then focused

217
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:41,640
on running an agro-processing factory
to help the villagers.

218
00:18:45,840 --> 00:18:47,880
Helping the villagers, huh?

219
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:51,520
More like covering up
for his drug dealing business.

220
00:18:59,120 --> 00:19:03,560
Well, everyone knows
Kamnan Pong hates drugs.

221
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:06,880
He's helped the government
in the fight against drugs

222
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,360
and won an award
for being an outstanding leader.

223
00:19:10,480 --> 00:19:11,960
Hates drugs,

224
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:15,680
but keeps drug dealers as his employees?

225
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:18,320
Believe whatever you want.

226
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,400
I don't buy it.

227
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,160
I believe what my own eyes have seen.

228
00:19:26,480 --> 00:19:29,480
I saw with my own eyes,
heard with my own ears,

229
00:19:29,560 --> 00:19:32,600
that Kamnan Pong ordered Phupha's murder.

230
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:38,720
And when I found out,
he ordered my death too.

231
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:48,440
Then why didn't you report it
to the police, Aunt Wilai?

232
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,480
If I wanted to film content inside,
would that be possible?

233
00:19:55,560 --> 00:19:57,680
How about this? We'll sit down another day

234
00:19:57,760 --> 00:20:00,000
and discuss the details
of what we'll be filming.

235
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,040
Sounds good.

236
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,760
Sergeant Biew and I
will take our leave now.

237
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:13,040
I can't. The police are all on their side.

238
00:20:14,320 --> 00:20:16,520
As long as we don't have evidence,

239
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,440
there's nothing we can do about them.

240
00:20:21,240 --> 00:20:23,160
Well then, my nephew and I
will take our leave.

241
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:26,040
- Go ahead.
- Goodbye.

242
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:27,960
- Goodbye.
- See you.

243
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:34,200
I just hope we get the teddy bear soon.

244
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:42,000
I'll use the evidence
to expose everything online.

245
00:20:42,080 --> 00:20:43,920
I'll show everyone the truth.

246
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:47,240
I want everyone to know

247
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,880
what Kamnan Pong is really like.

248
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:57,960
Let's go. I don't want
to stay here any longer.

249
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:15,240
Wait!

250
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:27,200
Next time,

251
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,680
don't come anywhere near me.

252
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:45,920
Hey, buddy.

253
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:47,960
Huh?

254
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,200
Thinking about a girl?

255
00:21:52,520 --> 00:21:55,720
What girl? I'm working!

256
00:21:55,800 --> 00:21:58,600
Yeah, working, huh?

257
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,520
Here.

258
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:04,120
You can't lie to me.

259
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,360
Who do you think I am?

260
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,680
I'm Lieutenant Manat,

261
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:10,080
the love expert
from the Central Investigation Division.

262
00:22:11,720 --> 00:22:13,560
Your eyes give you away.

263
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,040
Who are you thinking about?

264
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:18,560
Do I know her?

265
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:21,320
Or is it…

266
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:23,760
- Ms. Paula?
- Are you crazy?

267
00:22:25,080 --> 00:22:26,400
It's not her.

268
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,520
Or maybe…

269
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,120
the local angel from around here?

270
00:22:33,080 --> 00:22:36,280
- Hey, hey.
- Stop! Enough. No more guessing.

271
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:39,920
Go. Just go wherever.

272
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:42,680
Do you have work to do? Go ahead.

273
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,000
Go.

274
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:26,280
Kamnan Pong.

275
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:30,520
I think you should stop watching it.

276
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,600
I don't want you to get stuck in the past.

277
00:23:37,760 --> 00:23:40,760
Kamnan, a woman like that

278
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:44,800
isn't worth you thinking about.

279
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:48,240
Let me find you someone new.

280
00:23:48,320 --> 00:23:50,040
It'll be better for you.

281
00:23:50,120 --> 00:23:52,480
I shouldn't be thinking
about any new love.

282
00:23:58,840 --> 00:23:59,920
Actually, I have

283
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:04,640
the factory accounts for you to review
and a check for you to sign.

284
00:24:05,880 --> 00:24:07,320
Put it down there.

285
00:24:10,880 --> 00:24:12,920
I've come to invite you

286
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:14,720
to chair our label's singing contest.

287
00:24:15,840 --> 00:24:17,560
- When?
- Next week.

288
00:24:23,280 --> 00:24:25,240
I'm sure that at Darathong Music,

289
00:24:26,040 --> 00:24:29,280
they're hiding some important secret
we never expected.

290
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:39,720
- What's up, Sergeant Au?
- Captain.

291
00:24:40,400 --> 00:24:43,680
- They're having a party tonight.
- Where?

292
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,320
I'll follow them.

293
00:24:46,400 --> 00:24:50,280
They're heading toward the foothills,
near Khok Ta Yu village.

294
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:54,160
As soon as I get a confirmed location,

295
00:24:54,240 --> 00:24:55,760
I'll let you know.

296
00:24:55,840 --> 00:24:57,040
Okay.

297
00:24:58,120 --> 00:24:59,480
What's going on?

298
00:24:59,560 --> 00:25:01,840
Sergeant Au invited us to a party.

299
00:25:02,480 --> 00:25:04,160
It's near the foothills of Khok Ta Yoo.

300
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:07,920
Let's go, buddy! I've been itching
for something like this!

301
00:25:08,000 --> 00:25:09,080
Let's go.

302
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:17,000
Hey!

303
00:25:19,960 --> 00:25:20,960
Get out!

304
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,280
Sorry, guys.

305
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:28,720
What's this about?

306
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:32,040
No one's allowed through here. Got it?

307
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:35,880
Oh, I don't get it.

308
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:41,360
Why do you look like a cop?

309
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,400
Yeah, you're right.

310
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:47,760
I was thinking the same thing.

311
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:50,840
And if I look like a cop,

312
00:25:50,920 --> 00:25:52,880
then you two

313
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:54,440
look like robbers.

314
00:26:00,720 --> 00:26:02,520
Oops! Force of habit!

315
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:27,200
Is this the place Sergeant Au
mentioned we need to walk to?

316
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,400
Yeah.

317
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:32,520
If we drive in, they might notice us.

318
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:35,280
Then wait a sec.

319
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:45,240
Take this with you.

320
00:26:45,960 --> 00:26:47,800
Sergeant Au said
Deputy Phuchong just sent it.

321
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,160
You little bastard.

322
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:58,800
Got something good and didn't share?
I'll smack you!

323
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:01,680
Take it easy. I just saw it with you.

324
00:27:01,760 --> 00:27:03,280
You want a taste?

325
00:27:05,360 --> 00:27:06,680
Here, this is yours.

326
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:08,760
Take it.

327
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:16,680
Thank you, Deputy Phuchong,

328
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:18,400
for always looking out for us.

329
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:28,160
Ready, Manat?

330
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:32,280
- Been ready for a while, buddy.
- Then…

331
00:27:34,120 --> 00:27:35,280
let's go.

332
00:27:48,320 --> 00:27:50,600
- Everything good to go?
- It's all set.

333
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:02,600
How's it going, Sergeant?

334
00:28:04,200 --> 00:28:05,720
There's probably drugs in the car.

335
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:08,440
But why are they still staying quiet?

336
00:28:13,720 --> 00:28:15,160
That guy must be their leader.

337
00:28:16,640 --> 00:28:18,680
It looks like
they're waiting for something.

338
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:20,200
Waiting to go to jail.

339
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,560
I think you're right.

340
00:28:39,040 --> 00:28:40,040
Hello, Boss Ah.

341
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:42,240
You're right on time.

342
00:28:42,320 --> 00:28:43,760
Of course.

343
00:28:43,840 --> 00:28:46,200
But isn't the boss here today?

344
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:49,640
He's not. He's caught up with something.

345
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:52,040
That's too bad.
I was hoping to meet him today.

346
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:53,560
I'll check the goods first.

347
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:55,760
No problem. Go ahead.

348
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:08,000
- How's it going?
- The goods are great.

349
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:09,440
This batch is excellent.

350
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:13,040
I should thank you
for trusting us, Boss Ah.

351
00:29:13,120 --> 00:29:16,440
If it goes like this,
it will help my boss's products

352
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:18,720
get more recognition in the market.

353
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,680
Let your boss know

354
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:23,800
that I'll find a chance to visit.

355
00:29:24,880 --> 00:29:26,360
Sure, I'll let him know.

356
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:30,360
I'm starting to want to see their boss.

357
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:34,440
Here's the full cash amount.

358
00:29:35,720 --> 00:29:36,760
Check it.

359
00:29:43,240 --> 00:29:44,560
The money's all here.

360
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,880
- Everything's good.
- Good.

361
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,560
You can take the goods now.

362
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:52,840
Hey, load it onto the truck.

363
00:29:55,040 --> 00:29:56,160
Put the money away.

364
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:06,080
- Take care, Boss Ah.
- See you.

365
00:30:06,680 --> 00:30:08,680
Hey, Captain!

366
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,440
Are we gonna let this slide?

367
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:14,360
Not yet. It's not over.

368
00:30:18,360 --> 00:30:21,360
Sorry, Boss Ah. I didn't
get the chance to say goodbye.

369
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:32,080
Go to hell.

370
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,840
Let's go.

371
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,160
Who's that?

372
00:30:46,080 --> 00:30:48,080
I'm asking, who's that?

373
00:30:49,920 --> 00:30:51,200
Take them down!

374
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,640
Whoever kills them gets the reward!

375
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:09,440
Uncle Sergeant.

376
00:31:37,800 --> 00:31:40,440
That Chart guy, he's the right-hand man

377
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:41,400
of Kitti and Singha.

378
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,640
He's known them since they were young.

379
00:31:44,840 --> 00:31:46,640
He's been around for so long.

380
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:48,000
This means Chart

381
00:31:48,080 --> 00:31:50,200
must know everything inside and out.

382
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:51,760
It's possible

383
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:55,840
that he's involved
in the Phupha and Onanong case too.

384
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:59,920
Then I'll leave.
I don't want to be seen. I'm out.

385
00:32:11,720 --> 00:32:12,960
Come on!

386
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:14,800
I was going to take him in
for questioning.

387
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,640
Too late for that, Lieutenant.

388
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:20,320
Let's get out of here
before the local cops arrive.

389
00:32:20,400 --> 00:32:21,960
- Let's go.
- Yes.

390
00:32:31,200 --> 00:32:33,480
DARATHONG MUSIC

391
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:39,480
I need a sip of warm water, Teacher.
I'm so nervous right now.

392
00:32:39,560 --> 00:32:43,040
You've been through
so many singing competitions already.

393
00:32:43,120 --> 00:32:44,760
Why are you nervous now?

394
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:48,800
But this is the stage
that could shape my future as a singer.

395
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:51,720
Look at me, Teacher!
I'm so nervous, I'm getting goosebumps.

396
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:54,960
I wish Aunt Wilai were here.
I'd feel a bit more at ease.

397
00:32:55,680 --> 00:32:57,800
If she came, people would recognize her.

398
00:32:57,880 --> 00:33:00,560
You've got me here.
Doesn't that make you feel better?

399
00:33:01,440 --> 00:33:02,800
It does.

400
00:33:08,960 --> 00:33:09,800
Hey.

401
00:33:11,080 --> 00:33:12,840
The boss told us to set up checkpoints.

402
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:15,080
Search everyone going in and out.

403
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:19,120
Don't let any of Boss Noo's people
sneak into the event.

404
00:33:19,720 --> 00:33:21,240
Understood. Leave it to me.

405
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,160
Tod, Wong.

406
00:33:23,240 --> 00:33:25,640
- Set up the checkpoints.
- Got it.

407
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:35,040
CHECKPOINT

408
00:33:41,960 --> 00:33:43,080
Keep a close eye on Pleaw.

409
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:45,320
He's a slippery one.

410
00:33:45,880 --> 00:33:48,040
If you see him
lurking around the competition,

411
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:50,000
get rid of him.

412
00:33:51,520 --> 00:33:53,200
I remember all his men's faces.

413
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:54,640
No need to worry.

414
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:01,440
There he is.

415
00:34:01,520 --> 00:34:04,040
If Chart showed up in person,

416
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,800
that means all the VIPs
are definitely here.

417
00:34:05,880 --> 00:34:08,520
VIPs? More like gang bosses.

418
00:34:10,679 --> 00:34:14,400
Sergeant Au, call Sergeant Yot.
Tell him there might be a clash tonight.

419
00:34:14,480 --> 00:34:15,600
Roger that.

420
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:27,480
Yes, Boss.

421
00:34:28,719 --> 00:34:31,960
They've set up checkpoints
to screen everyone coming in.

422
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:36,560
I'll make sure their event

423
00:34:37,320 --> 00:34:38,520
falls apart tonight.

424
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:46,239
Captain, I've already reported
to Sergeant Yot.

425
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:48,440
The police unit is standing by and ready.

426
00:34:50,159 --> 00:34:51,760
Pleaw, who's that?

427
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:09,000
Look, that's Chart!

428
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,320
Chart.

429
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,760
- That bastard.
- Stop!

430
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:22,200
What are you doing?

431
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:25,600
Chart. He killed Tha--

432
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:29,120
He killed Phupha.

433
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:31,680
- I'll kill him!
- Stop!

434
00:35:32,720 --> 00:35:35,240
Poona is about to go on stage today.

435
00:35:35,320 --> 00:35:37,040
If we cause trouble now,

436
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:38,880
everything will be over.

437
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,800
And if both of us end up dead,

438
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:44,680
who's going to expose them?

439
00:35:46,680 --> 00:35:47,920
Come on.

440
00:35:48,640 --> 00:35:51,040
We've been holding on
for 20 years already.

441
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:54,200
Just a little longer.

442
00:35:55,080 --> 00:35:56,600
Don't let this blow up now.

443
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:04,640
I get it.

444
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:10,040
- I'll turn the car around.
- No need to turn back.

445
00:36:11,200 --> 00:36:14,080
I'm sure he doesn't recognize you now.

446
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,240
You drive up to him.

447
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:18,200
I'll get out here.

448
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:20,040
We'll meet inside.

449
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:40,160
Roll the window down.

450
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:45,040
- Where are you going?
- To the contest.

451
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:53,480
Chit, what's going on?

452
00:37:10,920 --> 00:37:13,440
Why are you covering your face?
Take it off.

453
00:37:14,960 --> 00:37:16,120
I said, take it off!

454
00:37:25,280 --> 00:37:26,280
What happened to your face?

455
00:37:26,360 --> 00:37:29,000
My house burned down.
I couldn't get out in time.

456
00:37:30,600 --> 00:37:32,280
Let me see clearly.

457
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:35,640
Hey, what is he doing?

458
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:45,440
With a face that ugly…

459
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:51,160
you still dare to show up at the event?
Not afraid of scaring everyone?

460
00:38:00,760 --> 00:38:03,360
Those bastards, picking on a woman.

461
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:05,800
Wait, look at that.

462
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:11,960
Hey!

463
00:38:12,640 --> 00:38:13,960
What are you guys doing?

464
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:16,840
Nothing, sir.

465
00:38:19,400 --> 00:38:22,640
Have you all lost your minds?
Can't you see the traffic's backed up?

466
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:23,920
Stop messing around.

467
00:38:24,880 --> 00:38:25,920
Move it!

468
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,920
- Yes.
- Yes, sir.

469
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:30,160
Move. Go on, hurry up!

470
00:38:31,400 --> 00:38:32,760
Go on!

471
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:36,000
Move it! Open it up.

472
00:38:39,640 --> 00:38:40,600
Sergeant Au.

473
00:38:41,360 --> 00:38:43,320
Keep an eye on those lackeys.

474
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:45,360
Let's go, Manat.

475
00:38:57,160 --> 00:38:58,960
You go check the left side.

476
00:38:59,040 --> 00:39:00,360
I'll take this side.

477
00:39:01,080 --> 00:39:02,720
Then we'll meet inside.

478
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:04,880
Got it.

479
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:09,160
You bastard!

480
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:11,320
I remember you.

481
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,960
- We meet again.
- I'm ending this right here.

482
00:39:19,960 --> 00:39:21,400
Boss, gunshots!

483
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:23,880
Let's go.

484
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:50,320
- You're dead!
- Take cover!

485
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,720
Hey, let's go!

486
00:40:25,480 --> 00:40:26,560
Let's go.

487
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:30,000
Oh.

488
00:40:31,560 --> 00:40:32,400
Oops.

489
00:40:33,960 --> 00:40:36,440
Poona, we meet again.

490
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:39,320
Are you here to be an extra?

491
00:40:40,840 --> 00:40:42,720
They don't call it an extra anymore.

492
00:40:42,800 --> 00:40:44,440
It's called a backup singer.

493
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:48,920
That's right. Miss Maria's
definitely going to win this.

494
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,640
You might as well get ready to accept it.

495
00:40:53,480 --> 00:40:55,680
If it's about outfits,

496
00:40:56,400 --> 00:40:57,640
you win by a mile.

497
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:59,200
Of course.

498
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:00,600
I'll give you that.

499
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:04,640
But wait, isn't this
a singing competition?

500
00:41:05,360 --> 00:41:07,720
Not a backup dancer contest.

501
00:41:07,800 --> 00:41:09,480
- Ouch!
- That's harsh.

502
00:41:09,560 --> 00:41:11,520
Are you saying my outfit
looks like a backup dancer?

503
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:15,320
Hey, watch your mouth!

504
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:17,880
If Miss Maria wasn't about to win,

505
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:19,560
I'd have slapped you already.

506
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:23,040
Go ahead, hit me.
I'll hit back. Fair game.

507
00:41:23,120 --> 00:41:25,440
Just so you know,
singers are judged by their voice,

508
00:41:25,520 --> 00:41:27,160
not their clothes.

509
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,960
Outfits,

510
00:41:30,040 --> 00:41:33,160
performing, and dancing,
they're just extras.

511
00:41:33,240 --> 00:41:35,440
Someone with an amazing voice
might not be able to dress or dance

512
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:37,680
and still win competitions.

513
00:41:40,080 --> 00:41:42,280
Are you really a music teacher

514
00:41:42,360 --> 00:41:45,120
or a professional insult machine?
That mouth cuts.

515
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:47,000
Let's go warm up over there.

516
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:49,240
No point wasting time here.

517
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:18,800
- Camera ready?
- Ready.

518
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:21,840
Go for it.

519
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:24,800
Tonight, we're YouTubers.

520
00:42:39,360 --> 00:42:42,040
Hey.

521
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:44,480
Target locked,
and you're not stopping, huh?

522
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:46,520
- Hey.
- Look.

523
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:48,000
There's plenty of pretty faces over there.

524
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:50,080
- Hey.
- Go on, film that side.

525
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:52,160
We gotta commit to the role properly.

526
00:42:54,200 --> 00:42:55,400
Go on. Get going.

527
00:42:55,480 --> 00:42:57,680
Handle that side. I'll take care of this.

528
00:42:57,760 --> 00:42:58,600
Go.

529
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:03,840
DARATHONG COUNTRY MUSIC SINGING CONTEST

530
00:43:03,920 --> 00:43:06,000
- What are you filming?
- Is something wrong?

531
00:43:08,640 --> 00:43:10,760
You are not allowed to film

532
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:12,640
without permission.

533
00:43:14,800 --> 00:43:17,400
We're YouTubers.

534
00:43:17,480 --> 00:43:21,560
We saw this big competition
and wanted to livestream to promote it.

535
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:23,120
Did you get permission from the organizer?

536
00:43:24,280 --> 00:43:26,480
I don't know
where we were supposed to ask.

537
00:43:26,560 --> 00:43:27,600
If you don't know, then don't film.

538
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:29,840
No manners at all.

539
00:43:31,040 --> 00:43:32,160
You country fools.

540
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:36,280
Are we really fighting?

541
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:40,880
- Ugh!
- Stop it! Stop!

542
00:43:40,960 --> 00:43:41,920
That's enough. Stop!

543
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:44,600
Chang.

544
00:43:47,040 --> 00:43:48,480
What's going on?

545
00:43:49,040 --> 00:43:49,960
These guys, Boss.

546
00:43:50,600 --> 00:43:54,040
They were filming something
without permission.

547
00:43:54,120 --> 00:43:55,600
We're YouTubers.

548
00:43:56,720 --> 00:43:59,240
They're YouTubers.
If they want to film, let them film.

549
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:03,800
Film wherever you want.
Even backstage is fine. I allow it.

550
00:44:03,880 --> 00:44:07,000
Make sure you help promote
our Darathong Music too.

551
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:09,880
- Yes.
- Yes.

552
00:44:10,640 --> 00:44:11,600
Feel free.

553
00:44:16,480 --> 00:44:17,400
That's enough.

554
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:48,800
Poona.

555
00:44:49,600 --> 00:44:50,800
Can you pass me my heels?

556
00:44:52,480 --> 00:44:53,760
That pair there, near you.

557
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:58,600
- They look great.
- Thanks.

558
00:44:58,680 --> 00:45:00,520
So beautiful.

559
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:08,480
- Ouch!
- Miss Maria, what's wrong?

560
00:45:08,560 --> 00:45:09,480
Something cut my foot!

561
00:45:09,560 --> 00:45:11,800
Oh no! Blood!

562
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:14,120
Do we call an ambulance? Oh my God!

563
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:15,960
There's so much blood!

564
00:45:16,040 --> 00:45:17,640
Where's the tissue?

565
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:19,600
Tissue! Tissue!

566
00:45:19,680 --> 00:45:22,360
Oh my God, blood!

567
00:45:22,440 --> 00:45:24,520
That's a lot of blood!

568
00:45:24,600 --> 00:45:25,600
Poona.

569
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:28,800
Did you really have to do this to me?

570
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,120
What?

571
00:45:30,200 --> 00:45:32,800
You're so desperate to win
that you'd use dirty tricks?

572
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:36,240
Wait, I didn't do anything, Maria.

573
00:45:37,760 --> 00:45:39,960
If I hadn't moved my foot in time,

574
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:41,960
I would've lost my toe.
I couldn't compete.

575
00:45:42,040 --> 00:45:43,320
Huh?

576
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:46,200
Why are you being so cruel to me?

577
00:45:46,280 --> 00:45:47,640
Exactly! Why are you being so cruel?

578
00:45:47,720 --> 00:45:50,320
Have you forgotten our friendship?

579
00:45:51,280 --> 00:45:52,920
I swear I didn't do it.

580
00:45:53,000 --> 00:45:55,480
I want to win,
but I wouldn't do anything like that.

581
00:45:55,560 --> 00:45:58,960
There! Everyone heard it!
She just said she wants to win.

582
00:45:59,760 --> 00:46:01,800
That's your true intention!

583
00:46:01,880 --> 00:46:04,760
You did this because you want to win.
You'll do anything.

584
00:46:05,680 --> 00:46:07,920
Am I right, everyone? She's the worst!

585
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:12,800
She should be disqualified.

586
00:46:13,520 --> 00:46:14,800
We don't accept

587
00:46:14,880 --> 00:46:16,040
this kind of dirty play.

588
00:46:16,120 --> 00:46:20,040
Yeah, she looks good,
but how can her heart be so ugly?

589
00:46:20,120 --> 00:46:21,560
I can't believe it.

590
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:25,800
- Disqualify Poona!
- Disqualify Poona!

591
00:46:25,880 --> 00:46:26,920
Disqualify Poona!

592
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:28,840
Disqualify Poona!

593
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:31,240
Disqualify Poona!

594
00:46:31,320 --> 00:46:33,120
Disqualify Poona!

595
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:37,560
Poona, are you going to step out
of the competition yet?

596
00:46:37,640 --> 00:46:40,920
So we don't waste everyone's time, right?

597
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:44,480
Poona hasn't even competed yet.
You can't disqualify her like this.

598
00:46:47,200 --> 00:46:49,960
Hey, you two, go guard the checkpoint.

599
00:46:50,760 --> 00:46:52,320
Wong and I will go check things inside.

600
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:53,360
Got it, Chart.

601
00:46:53,440 --> 00:46:54,280
- Let's go.
- Yes.

602
00:47:07,760 --> 00:47:09,560
He's still alive?

603
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:12,440
- Wong, come with me!
- Hey!

604
00:47:14,960 --> 00:47:18,920
Here, Judge. This contestant is a bully.

605
00:47:19,880 --> 00:47:23,400
Judge, Miss Maria was bullied.

606
00:47:23,480 --> 00:47:26,320
We caught her red-handed.
The person who bullied her

607
00:47:26,400 --> 00:47:27,680
is this woman.

608
00:47:29,760 --> 00:47:31,000
Is this true?

609
00:47:32,040 --> 00:47:35,440
It's not true. I didn't do anything.
I don't know what's going on.

610
00:47:36,680 --> 00:47:38,200
Who would admit

611
00:47:38,760 --> 00:47:40,920
to something like that so easily?

612
00:47:42,880 --> 00:47:45,080
- Exactly.
- If there's no solid evidence,

613
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:47,720
- no one's going to admit to it, right?
- That's true.

614
00:47:48,760 --> 00:47:50,360
According to the competition rules,

615
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:52,800
all contestants must show sportsmanship.

616
00:47:52,880 --> 00:47:55,280
If there's bullying like this,

617
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:56,880
I'll disqualify you.

618
00:48:01,440 --> 00:48:05,400
Disqualify Poona! Disqualify Poona!

619
00:48:05,480 --> 00:48:07,720
Disqualify Poona! Disqualify Poona!

620
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:15,760
<i>Honestly, it's so annoying</i>

621
00:48:15,840 --> 00:48:18,840
Her moves are heart-stopping.
I think she's a clear winner.

622
00:48:18,920 --> 00:48:21,800
This song is what made
Onanong Wongwichian famous.

623
00:48:22,600 --> 00:48:24,040
She's the ex-lover of Kamnan Pong.

624
00:48:33,720 --> 00:48:35,480
- Damn it!
- Don't go!

625
00:48:35,560 --> 00:48:36,560
It's too dangerous.

626
00:51:38,800 --> 00:51:41,560
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
